<item>
            <title>[LU-7031] lctl set_param -P behaves differently than lctl conf_param</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7031</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; functionality, which landed via [&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3155&quot; title=&quot;Permanent parameters with lctl set_param -P&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;| for 2.5.0, behaves different than the &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl conf_param&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; functionality it deprecates. According to email exchanges, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; is part of a design change to move away from /proc as a method of storing configuration. This issue exist to discuss continuation, alternatives, or removal of &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
